This is Perl module FSM::Tiny.

INSTALLATION

Type the following command:

    $ curl -L http://cpanmin.us | perl - FSM::Tiny

Or install cpanm and then run the following command to install
FSM::Tiny:

    $ cpanm FSM::Tiny

If you get an archive of this distribution, unpack it and build it
as per the usual:

    $ tar xzf FSM-Tiny-$version.tar.gz
    $ cd FSM-Tiny-$version
    $ perl Makefile.PL
    $ make && make test

Then install it:

    $ make install

DOCUMENTATION

FSM::Tiny documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    $ perldoc FSM::Tiny

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

